OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sat 7 Mar to Mon 16 MarFAs
OL,6,Fwe head into the second week of March,
OL,7,Fhigh pressure looks to maintain its
OL,8,Finfluence, especially towards the
OL,9,Fsouth or southeast of the UK. This
OL,10,Fmeans that many places will see plenty
OL,11,Fof dry weather with variable cloud
OL,12,Famounts and some sunshine. The best of
OL,13,Fthe sunny weather is most likely
OL,14,Ftowards the south or southeast. Some
OL,15,Fovernight fog is possible given clear
OL,16,Fskies and light winds. However,
OL,17,Ffrontal systems are still likely to
OL,18,Faffect the north and west of the UK at
OL,19,Ftimes, perhaps pushing further east on
OL,20,Foccasion. This might lead to some rain
OL,21,Fand strong winds, and possibly some
OL,22,Fhill snow across the highest parts of
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,FScotland and Northern Ireland.
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,FTemperatures will be near or above
OL,25,Fnormal, although a few frosty nights
OL,26,Fare still likely.
